Sexual HIV transmission is an urgent problem in the Chinese LGBT community.
Homosexuality has been decriminalized in China in 1997, but discrimination against LGBT people is still widespread.
Because of the traditional values of the country, some studies have estimated that 70-90% of men who have sexual intercourse with other men eventually marry women.
Many of the transmissions of diseases are caused by inadequate protections during sexual relations within such relationships.
In 2003, the Chinese government promised universal access to HIV drugs as part of its commitment to managing the problem.
